<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>pony up for something • pony up something</xh5><p> <i>pony up for something</i>—(U.S. coll.) make a request for smth.: Actually, I’m reading the e-book, but I already know I will <u>pony up for</u> the print version as well.</p><p> <i>pony up something</i>—(U.S. coll.) repay the money one owes: Tell him to defer enrollment for a year. Otherwise, he’s got to <u>pony up</u> the whole amount through a bank loan.</p> </entry>
